  "local_port": 40032,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I use WhatsApp on a PC?",
  "response": "You can use WhatsApp on a PC in two primary ways: via WhatsApp Web or by using the WhatsApp Desktop application. Here\u2019s how you can do both:\n\n### Using WhatsApp Web\n\n1. **Open your web browser**: Go to [web.whatsapp.com](https://web.whatsapp.com).\n2. **Scan the QR code**: \n   - On your phone, open WhatsApp.\n   - Tap on the three dots (Menu) in the top-right corner on Android, or go to Settings on iPhone.\n   - Select \"WhatsApp Web\".\n   - Point your phone's camera at the QR code displayed on your PC screen.\n3. **Start chatting**: Once the QR code is scanned, your chats will appear on your PC, allowing you to send and receive messages.\n\n### Using the WhatsApp Desktop Application\n\n1. **Download and install the app**: \n   - Go to the [WhatsApp Download page](https://www.whatsapp.com/download).\n   - Choose the correct version for your operating system (Windows or Mac) and download it.\n   - Install the application by following the on-screen instructions.\n2. **Open the app and scan the QR code**: \n   - Just like with WhatsApp Web, you will see a QR code when you open the app.\n   - Open WhatsApp on your phone.\n   - Tap the three dots for Android or go to Settings for iPhone and choose \"WhatsApp Web\".\n   - Scan the QR code on your computer screen.\n3. **Start chatting**: After scanning, your chats will sync, and you can use WhatsApp on your desktop.\n\n### Requirements:\n- Make sure your phone is connected to the internet (Wi-Fi or mobile data) while using WhatsApp on your PC.\n- Ensure that you have the latest version of WhatsApp installed on your phone.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n- To log out from WhatsApp Web or the Desktop app, you can go to the menu (three dots in WhatsApp Web or the menu in the app) and select \"Log out\".\n- You can receive and send messages, view status updates, and more, just like on your mobile device.\n\nFollowing these steps will enable you to use WhatsApp on your PC easily!",
